# WC-Advisor Project Context

- Build features for a bathroom finder/review app with Angular frontend and FastAPI backend.
- Keep architecture boundaries: frontend in `frontend/`, backend in `backend/`, gateway in `nginx-gateway/`.
- Follow production routing model: `/api/*` to FastAPI, all other routes to Angular SPA.
- Preserve the rule "one review per user per WC" in any backend or DB changes.
- Prioritize finishing the WC state/filtering refactor before unrelated improvements.

# Change Discipline

- Prefer small, focused diffs over broad refactors.
- Avoid introducing new frameworks/state libraries (no NgRx).
- Keep docs and naming consistent with existing feature-first structure.
